<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		{>htmlHead/}
		<title>ASQ - Upload new presentation </title>

	</head>
	<body>

		<!--   top menu -->
		{>menu/}

		<!--   Content area   -->
		<div class="container" id="mainContainer">

			<div class="row">
				<!--   Seperating Headline   -->
				<div class="col-md-12 headline">
					<h2>Upload new presentation</h2>
				</div>

			</div>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="col-md-12">
					<form method="POST" action="/{username}/presentations/" enctype="multipart/form-data" class="form-inline form-upload">
						<!-- <input id="lefile" type="file" name="upload" size="40" maxlength="100000" style="display:none">
						<div class="input-append">
							<input id="photoCover" class="input-large" type="text">
							<a class="btn btn-default" onclick="$('input[id=lefile]').click();">Browse</a>
							<button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Upload</button>
						</div> -->

						<div class="input-group">
						    <span class="input-group-btn">
						        <span class="btn btn-default btn-file">
						            Browse&hellip; <input type="file" id="lefile" type="file" name="upload" size="40" maxlength="100000">
						        </span>
						    </span>
						    <input type="text" class="form-control" readonly>
						</div>
						<button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Upload</button>
						<script>
						$(document).on('change', '.btn-file :file', function() {
						  var input = $(this),
						      numFiles = input.get(0).files ? input.get(0).files.length : 1,
						      label = input.val().replace(/\\/g, '/').replace(/.*\//, '');
						  input.trigger('fileselect', [numFiles, label]);
						});

						$(document).ready( function() {
						    $('.btn-file :file').on('fileselect', function(event, numFiles, label) {
						        
						        var input = $(this).parents('.input-group').find(':text'),
						            log = numFiles > 1 ? numFiles + ' files selected' : label;
						        
						        if( input.length ) {
						            input.val(log);
						        } else {
						            if( log ) alert(log);
						        }
						        
						    });
						});
						</script>
					</form>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="row" >
				<div class="col-md-12 headline">
					<h2>Upload with curl</h2>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-12">
					</p> To zip all the files in the current directory and upload them with curl as a new  presentation:<br>
					<pre class="upload-code"><code>zip -r - * | curl -i --cookie "{user.cookie}" -F "title=<span class="upload-fa-stack fa-stack fa-lg"> <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x"></i> <i class="fa fa-stack-1x text">1</i></span>" -F upload=@- {rootUrl}/{user.name}/presentations</code></pre>
					</p>
					
				</div>

				<div class="col-md-12">
					</p> or replace an existing presentation with a zip file:<br>
					<pre class="upload-code"><code>zip -r - * | curl -X PUT -i --cookie "{user.cookie}" -F "title=<span class="upload-fa-stack fa-stack fa-lg"> <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x"></i> <i class="fa fa-stack-1x text">1</i></span>" -F upload=@- {rootUrl}/{user.name}/presentations/<span class="upload-fa-stack fa-stack fa-lg"> <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x"></i> <i class="fa fa-stack-1x text">2</i></span><span class="upload-fa-stack fa-stack fa-lg"> <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x"></i> <i class="fa fa-stack-1x text">3</i></span></code></pre>
					</p>	
				</div>
				
				<div class="col-md-12">
					<span class="upload-fa-stack fa-stack fa-lg"> <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x"></i> <i class="fa fa-stack-1x text">1</i></span> The title of the presentation, eg. <code class="upload-inline-code">Introduction to JavaScript</code> <br>
					<span class="upload-fa-stack fa-stack fa-lg"> <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x"></i> <i class="fa fa-stack-1x text">2</i></span> The id of the presentation, eg. <code class="upload-inline-code">0123456789abcdef01234567</code> <br>
					<span class="upload-fa-stack fa-stack fa-lg"> <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x"></i> <i class="fa fa-stack-1x text">3</i></span> You can append <code class="upload-inline-code">?preserveSession=true</code> to the URL to preserve the session; good for testing on a live presentation</code>
				</div>
			</div>

		</div>

		<script src="/js/asq-client.js"></script>
		<script>
				var $=require("jQuery");
				$('input[id=lefile]').change(function() {
			   $('#photoCover').val($(this).val());
			});
		</script>
	</body>
</html>